ch isn’t in the test class names. Also, it seems okay for inner classes to have those. This support class is directly referencing the test class name. I need to consider removing headless order imports, maybe it's unnecessary. Lastly, I’ll implement timer delays to make sure the dialog closes properly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing dialog behavior with Timer**\\n\\nI'm considering if a failure might occur if the Timer doesn't close due to blocking in the modal. The Swing Timer runs on the Event Dispatch Thread (EDT), but the JOptionPane.showMessageDialog is being called from the test thread, which blocks. However, since the dialog has its own event pump on the EDT, I think it should be fine. Swing Timer events fire on the EDT within that modal event pump, which is reassuring.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_PjFzn09QCDzCmS6wFWTuALgS|fc_0d2b5657fa412a260169f63d76cec88191a35f3918d1dc7697", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/junit/junit/3.7/src/test/java/legacy/junit3/JunitSwinguiTestRunnerTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import junit.runner.FailureDetailView;\nimport junit.swingui.StatusLine;\nimport junit.swingui.TestRunner;\n", "newText": "import junit.runner.FailureDetailView;\nimport junit.runner.TestCollector;\nimport junit.swingui.StatusLine;\nimport junit.swingui.TestRunner;\n"}, {"oldText": "import javax.swing.JButton;\nimport javax.swing.JFrame;\nimport javax.swing.JPanel;\nimport javax.swing.SwingUtilities;\nimport java.awt.Component;\nimport java.awt.HeadlessException;\n", "newText": "import javax.swing.JButton;\nimport javax.swing.JFrame;\nimport javax.swing.JPanel;\nimport javax.swing.SwingUtilities;\nimport javax.swing.Timer;\nimport java.awt.Component;\nimport java.awt.Dialog;\nimport java.awt.Window;\n"}, {"oldText": "import java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicBoolean;\n", "newText": "import java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicBoolean;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\n"}, {"oldText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;\n", "newText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static final AtomicBoolean failNextRun = new AtomicBoolean();\n", "newText": "    private static final AtomicBoolean failNextRun = new AtomicBoolean();\n    private static final AtomicInteger constructedCollectors = new AtomicInteger();\n"}, {"oldText": "    void createsConfiguredTestCollectorBeforeOpeningHeadlessBrowserDialog() throws Exception {\n        ExposedTestRunner runner = newRunnerWithPreferences(\n                \"TestCollectorClass=junit.runner.SimpleTestCollector\");\n\n        String previousHeadless = System.getProperty(\"java.awt.headless\");\n        System.setProperty(\"java.awt.headless\", \"true\");\n        try {\n            assertThatThrownBy(runner::browseTestClasses).isInstanceOf(HeadlessException.class);\n        } finally {\n            restoreProperty(\"java.awt.headless\", previousHeadless);\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    void createsConfiguredTestCollectorBeforeOpeningBrowserDialog() throws Exception {\n        assertThat(new EmptyTestCollector().collectTests().hasMoreElements()).isFalse();\n        constructedCollectors.set(0);\n        ExposedTestRunner runner = newRunnerWithPreferences(\n                \"TestCollectorClass=\" + EmptyTestCollector.class.getName());\n        Timer dialogCloser = new Timer(50, ignored -> closeShowingDialogs());\n        dialogCloser.setRepeats(true);\n\n        try {\n            dialogCloser.start();\n            runner.browseTestClasses();\n        } finally {\n            dialogCloser.stop();\n            closeShowingDialogs();\n        }\n\n        assertThat(constructedCollectors.get()).isGreaterThanOrEqualTo(1);\n    }\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static v